  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening Consumer Information for Sustainable Consumption and Production</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Sustainable consumption and production is increasingly a priority for business and for policy-making. It is a cross-cutting theme of the Agenda 2030 and the Sustainable Development Goals, directly addressed by Goal 12 &amp;ndash; Ensure sustainable consumption and productions patterns. 

This Project will support the private sector, governments, label owners and influencers to increase the provision of reliable consumer information to encourage sustainable choices in consumption and production, as well as to foster circular economy, contributing to the achievement of the Sustainable Development Goal Target 12.8. At the same time, the Project is addressing key recommendations from the United Nations Environment Assembly.

Through this Project, UN Environment will partner with the private sector in the implementation of the Guidelines for Providing Product Sustainability Information, as well as promoting the use of consumer information tools as a means to improve business procurement and relation with the value chain. At the same time, the project supports governments to reform policies that distort product prices and encourage unsustainable consumption and wasteful use of resources. The use of consumer information tools can also help governments to consume more sustainably, enhancing the global uptake of more sustainable products. Both strategies aim to help reduce pollution and the pressure on natural resources through the use of consumer information tools. The work with influencers is also being included as a way to extend Project&amp;rsquo;s impact.</narrative>
  </description>
